        print("The hermit follows the cave down feeling the earth getting colder and colder. Suddenly the hermit finds themselves at a split in the cave and feels a gust of wind. Should the hermit go LEFT or RIGHT?")
        action = input(": ").upper()
    elif direction == "LEFT":
        print("The hermit goes left, neither climbing nor descending. All of the sudden their feet feels wet finding themselves walking into a river. Should the hermit SWIM across or FOLLOW the river?")
        action = input(": ").upper()
    elif direction == "RIGHT":
        print("The hermit goes right walking into the darkness. Swoosh, the hermit falls into a deep pit. Should the hermit CLIMB out or STAY and wait for help?")
